cs.DL, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.SD 

The paper discusses the scientific habilitation procedure for university appointments in Italy, which is related to the field of computer science in terms of academic appointments and research evaluation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DL (Digital Libraries) as it deals with the management of digital information and scholarly communication. The paper also discusses corruption and discrimination, which are relevant to the fields of cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The analysis of the outcomes of the habilitation procedure involves statistical methods, which are related to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Software Engineering).
